description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you seeking an exciting, rewarding and fulfilling job role where every day is different?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you passionate about the delivery of safe and effective patient centred care and ensuring the delivery of effective clinical governance?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, we are looking to recruit a highly motivated leader who is a competent, innovative and an enthusiastic Registered Nurse to become a ward manager on one of our acute care of the elderly wards. You will need to excel in communication skills and hold skills to enable the delivery of effective leadership. You will need to lead by example, be a role model for junior nurses to aspire to and be dynamic and forward thinking in your approach to providing the highest standard of nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortescue Ward is part of the Medical Division, and specialises in the care of people with Dementia, Frailty, and long term conditions requiring management and rehabilitation. Our aim is to promote and maintain independence in patients with a focus on home first as our priority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortescue ward has its own full time discharge and activities co-ordinators, admiral nurse, forward thinking MDT team and newly appointed care of the elderly consultant. The ward welcomes student nurses, apprentices and also supports workplace experiences for college students on work shadowing days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by a new care of the elderly matron who will have overall responsibility for ensuring that patient care, safety and experience is at the highest standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By coming to work for us we can offer you a supportive forward thinking environment, there will be plenty of opportunities to further develop your nursing career and strengthen styles of leadership which could be supported by our in house leadership programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information potential candidates are welcome to contact Rebecca Bennet (Clinical Matron) on 01271 313978 ext 4278 or bleep 324, or rebeccabennett2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 16/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
